Sure, here's an example of the code you can use to create a sidebar with the nav links home, about, and contact:

```
<aside>
  <nav>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
      <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
      <li><a href="/contact">Contact</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>
</aside>
```

You can also style the sidebar however you like using CSS. Here's an example:

```
aside {
  width: 200px;
  background-color: #f1f1f1;
  padding: 20px;
}

nav ul {
  list-style: none;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}

nav li {
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}

nav li a {
  color: #333;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-weight: bold;
}
```

To add a button that says "Hello World" to a webpage, you can use HTML code and style it with CSS. Here's an example:

HTML Code:

```
<button class="hello-button">Hello World</button>
```

CSS Code:

```
.hello-button {
  background-color: #4CAF50;
  border: none;
  color: white;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  text-align: center;
  text-decoration: none;
  display: inline-block;
  font-size: 16px;
  margin: 10px;
  cursor: pointer;
}
```

This code will create a green button with white text that says "Hello World". You can customize the colors, padding, font size, and other properties as needed.
